Hey team! Someone accidentally invited an external person (barry) to our Slack. We've deleted him.

A few changes made:
1. Going forward, invites require admin permission
2. I've moved our main channels to private channels
3. I've expanded the set of admins
When making a group with a customer, let's always create an external group - not invite them to our Slack.

In rare cases, we run into issues (can't make an external group). In that case, let's first try to make a TG group instead.
